blogs.title: Taurus peoples destiny
blogs.content: Taurus is the second astrological sign in the present zodiac. It spans from 30° to 60° of the zodiac. This sign belongs to the Earth element or triplicity, and has a feminine or negative polarity, as well as a fixed modality, quality, or quadruplicity. It is a Venus-ruled sign like Libra. The Sun transits this sign from approximately April 21 until May 20 in western astrology. People born between these dates, depending on which system of astrology they subscribe to, may be called Taureans. The symbol of the bull is based on the Cretan Bull, the white bull that fathered the Minotaur who was killed by Theseus. In this summer constellation's official depiction, it is facing right, with its head upraised; the nearby constellation of Orion can be imagined as a hunter raising his arm in victory over the bull's demise. The bull's horns were represented by the V-shaped group of stars located in the head of the constellation. Then you ll be rich...
blogs.author: Berke Jan
